Concentrations of gases such as CH4 and CO2 are measured in parts per million (ppm), a unit of concentration that is equivalent to a fraction of a million, indicating the ratio of the amount of the gas to the amount of air on a molecular basis.; 
The thresholds for CH4 (> 1000 ppm) and CO2 (> 500 ppm) are considered high and may indicate potential safety or environmental concerns.; 
The role 'data analyst' is specified, implying that only access by users with this role is of interest for this query.

sql:
SELECT MAX(calibration_date)
FROM calibration_logs
WHERE equipment_id = 0;

SELECT location_id, AVG(CH4) AS avg_ch4
FROM gas_measurements
WHERE location_id = 0;
